Feedback_Text:
I have several sorry:
- asking trustworthiness probably instinctively lowers my trustworthiness rating for them
- I forgot to pay attention to the ai or photo tags so I just got carried away with the face ratings - perhaps the tags flashed too quick so I didnt pay attention to them
- trustworthiness cant really be inferred from photographs. I feel like other parameters have a much bigger impact on whether you think people are trustworthy or not - videos could perhaps give more 'real' estimates
- I needed more breaks lol
- Most of the faces were pretty ugly and so perhaps not very attention grabbing - idk if they are all ai but I think most seemed less attractive than the average person
- idk if the background played into it as well - as in, having no background made them look more sus and also perhaps more ugly as you really focus on their facial features
- I think a rating as well for attractiveness and other scales as in 1-10 could be better rather than agree/disagree. - as in, if they are ugly then I would give a rating of disagree, but also if they are standard looking, then they arent beautiful so do I give the same rating?
- It was quite long, perhaps too many faces
- near the end I started to feel like they were all suspicious because they all had no background and then I started to think they were all ai. - kinda spiralled a bit so perhapos if it is a bit shorter then won't reach such thresholds.
